  "Salaries are perfectly symmetric with values evenly distributed around the center": "",
  "Most employees earn above $95,000 and the distribution clusters at the high end": "",
  "The distribution is left-skewed with a long tail extending toward lower salary values": "",
  "When the mean is much larger than the median, the distribution is right-skewed. A few executives earning very high salaries pull the mean upward.": "",
  "A marathon had 200 runners. The mean finish time was 4 hours 15 minutes, the median was 4 hours 10 minutes, and the mode was 4 hours 5 minutes. If you wanted to predict the MOST COMMON finish time for future runners, which measure would you report?": "",
  "The median, because it splits runners in half": "",
  "The range, because it shows the fastest and slowest": "",
  "The mean, because it is the most common statistic": "",
  "The mode, because it represents the finish time achieved by the largest group of runners": "",
  "The mode (4:05) identifies the single most common finish time, making it the best predictor of the most likely individual outcome.": "",
  "A data set of daily temperatures (°F) for a week is: 55, 58, 60, 62, 61, 59, 57. A weather forecaster adds an erroneous reading of 160°F. How does this error affect the mean versus the median?": "",
  "Both the mean and median increase dramatically": "",
  "Neither is affected because 160 is obviously wrong": "",
  "The mean increases dramatically (from about 58.9 to about 71.5), but the median changes only slightly": "",
  "The median increases more than the mean": "",
  "Original mean ≈ 58.9. With 160 added, mean = (55+57+58+59+60+61+62+160)/8 = 572/8 = 71.5. The median shifts from 59.5 to 59.5 (still between 59 and 60), demonstrating its resistance to outliers.": "",
  "A survey of 10 households reports annual incomes: $30k, $35k, $38k, $40k, $42k, $45k, $48k, $50k, $55k, $500k. A politician claims the mean income is about $88k, proving the area is wealthy. An opponent counters that the median is only $43.5k. Who gives a more representative picture?": "",
  "Both are equally misleading because neither the mean nor the median is appropriate": "",
  "The politician, because the mean uses all data values and is therefore always better": "",
  "The opponent, because the median ($43.5k) is not inflated by the single $500k outlier and better represents typical household income": "",
  "Neither, because income data should never be summarized using a single number": "",
  "Mean = $883k/10 = $88.3k, heavily skewed by the $500k value. Median = (42+45)/2 = $43.5k, which better represents the typical household.": "",
  "A factory produces bolts with target diameter 10.0 mm. A sample of 6 bolts measures: 9.8, 9.9, 10.0, 10.0, 10.1, 10.2. The quality engineer computes the mean, median, and mode. Which of the following is correct?": "",
  "Mean = 10.0, Median = 10.0, Mode = 10.0": "",
  "Mean = 9.9, Median = 10.0, Mode = 10.2": "",
  "Mean = 10.1, Median = 10.0, Mode = 9.9": "",
  "Mean = 10.0, Median = 9.95, Mode = 10.1": "",
  "Mean = (9.8+9.9+10.0+10.0+10.1+10.2)/6 = 60.0/6 = 10.0. Median = (10.0+10.0)/2 = 10.0. Mode = 10.0 (appears twice). All three equal the target.": "",
  "An ice cream shop tracks daily sales of five flavors over a month. Vanilla sold 450 units, Chocolate 430, Strawberry 200, Mint 180, and Mango 140. The owner wants to determine the most popular flavor and the average sales per flavor. What are the mode and the mean?": "",
  "Mode = Vanilla (450 units); Mean = 280 units per flavor": "",
  "Mode = Strawberry; Mean = 250 units": "",
  "Mode = Mango; Mean = 280 units": "",
  "Mode = Chocolate; Mean = 300 units": "",
  "The mode is Vanilla with the highest sales (450). Mean = (450+430+200+180+140)/5 = 1400/5 = 280 units per flavor.": ""
